{
  "texts": [
    "Verbs may operate similarly to how ascribes function for objects.",
    "Transitive verbs often need concrete things and human subjects to function as their predicated complements.",
    "(This is discrete from character-based behavior detection in humans, which is similar to anticipating object properties.)",
    "Verbs, objects, and human attitudes must all be identified in order to identify activities.",
    "Discriminative classifiers, such Support Vector Machines (SVMs), are mostly used in recognition."
  ]
}